{"key":"post-9391714","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9391714</id>\n<content>Don't heat your terrarium.&amp;nbsp; As has been said for years, doing so causes condensation on the sides, and that condensation is made by robbing humidity from the air in your terrarium.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You'll have to heat the area your terrarium is sitting in.&amp;nbsp; While &lt;i&gt;you&lt;/i&gt; may like the cold, your mushrooms are a tropical species and they won't.&amp;nbsp; Find a way to get the ambient temperature where your terrarium sits to 70F to 75F.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9394301</next>\n<prev>9391523</prev>\n<first>9391266</first>\n<last>9553281</last>\n<when>1228762420</when>\n<utime>12/08/08 08:53 PM</utime>\n</post>"}